                    "TradeItemDescriptionInformation": {
                      "AdditionalTradeItemDescription": [
                        {
                          "LanguageCode": "en",
                          "Value": "DRDP is a universal virus-inactivating medium intended for the collection and transport of upper respiratory specimens (saliva, nasal swabs) for in vitro diagnostic testing on the presence of antigens or genetic material (i.e. viral RNA, human RNA/DNA).\nDRDP can be used in quick lateral flow tests, and in molecular methods such as (RT-)qPCR.\nDRDP can be suitable for direct PCR in your specific test system upon validation (i.e. no extraction and/or purification needed).\nDRDP stabilizes nucleic acids up to 8 days after collection when stored between 2-25°C."
